🌺 Concluding Reflection
Dear Friends, I especially appreciate why Ācārya Shri Jayaprakash Pandey Ji dwells at length on these verses. They are not merely a classification of people into sāttvika, rājasika, and tāmasika. They offer a mirror for self-examination.

This harmonizes perfectly with Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha. Liberation does not begin by changing the world outside; it begins by recognizing the tendencies that quietly govern our own mind. When those tendencies are purified through viveka, devotion, and right understanding, the same world that once appeared as bondage becomes the very field of awakening. Hari Om Tat Sat. 🙏🌿
